.TH "NANI-CLI" "1" "2026" "nani-cli 1.1" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
nani-cli \- watch anime from the command line

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nani-cli
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
A shell script to browse, search, stream, and download anime from the command line.
.PD 0
.P
.PD
This tool scrapes publicly available anime streaming sources.
.PD 0
.P
.PD
\f[B]nani-cli\f[R] without options defaults to IINA on macOS, flatpak mpv on Steam Deck, mpv apk on Android, VLC on iOS, and mpv everywhere else.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-e | --episode | -r | --range\fR \fI\,<episode>\/\fR
Specify the episode numbers to watch. If a range is specified, it should be quoted or separated by a non-numeric character (e.g. \-).

.TP
\fB\-c | --continue\fR
Continue watching anime from history.

.TP
\fB\-d | --download\fR
Download episode(s) instead of playing.

.TP
\fB\-D | --delete\fR
Delete watch history.

.TP
\fB\-l | --logview\fR
Show playback logs.

.TP
\fB\-h | --help\fR
Show summary of options.

.TP
\fB\-q | --quality\fR \fI\,<best|worst|360|480|720|1080>\/\fR
Set the video quality. Default is best.

.TP
\fB\-s | --syncplay\fR
Watch anime together with friends using Syncplay (mpv only).

.TP
\fB\-U | --update\fR
Fetch updates from GitHub.

.TP
\fB\-v | --vlc\fR
Use VLC as the media player.

.TP
\fB\-S | --select-nth\fR \fI\,<index>\/\fR
Select the nth entry from search results.

.TP
\fB\-N | --nextep-countdown\fR
Print a countdown to the next episode if the anime is ongoing.

.TP
\fB\--dub\fR
Play the dubbed version if available. Default is subbed.

.TP
\fB\--rofi\fR
Use rofi instead of fzf for interactive menus.

.TP
\fB\--skip\fR
Use ani-skip to skip episode intros (mpv only).

.TP
\fB\--no-detach\fR
Do not detach the media player (useful for terminal-based playback, mpv only).

.TP
\fB\--exit-after-play\fR
Exit the player and return its exit code (useful for scripting).

.TP
\fB\--skip-title\fR \fI\,<title>\/\fR
Override the title used for ani-skip queries.

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
nani-cli uses environment variables to control advanced or experimental behavior.
Command-line options take precedence over environment variables.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_MODE\fR
Set playback mode: sub or dub. Default is sub.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_DOWNLOAD_DIR\fR
Directory where downloaded files are saved. Default is the current directory.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_QUALITY\fR
Preferred video quality. Default is best.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_PLAYER\fR
Media player to use. Valid values include mpv, vlc, iina, debug, download, android_mpv, android_vlc, flatpak_mpv, catt, or any player capable of streaming URLs.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_EXTERNAL_MENU\fR
Set menu frontend: 0 uses fzf, 1 uses rofi. Default is 0.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_EXTERNAL_MENU_NORMAL_WINDOW\fR
If set to 1, rofi opens as a normal window.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_LOG\fR
Enable episode logging. 1 enables logging, 0 disables. Default is 1.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_MULTI_SELECTION\fR
Multi-selection flag for the chosen menu frontend.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_HIST_DIR\fR
Directory used to store watch history. Defaults to
\fB$XDG_STATE_HOME/nani-cli\fR or \fB$HOME/.local/state/nani-cli\fR.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_DEFAULT_SOURCE\fR
Default source behavior. history is equivalent to --continue.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_SKIP_INTRO\fR
Enable ani-skip by default. 1 enables, 0 disables.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_NO_DETACH\fR
Prevent mpv from detaching from the terminal.

.TP
\fBNANI_CLI_SKIP_TITLE\fR
Override the title used for ani-skip lookups.

